Author-Name: Robert A. Margo  
Title: The Economic History of the <em>American Economic Review</em>: A Century's Explosion of Economics Research 
Abstract:
 Written in celebration of the 100th anniversary of the <em>American
 Economic Review</em>, this paper recounts the history of the journal. The
 recounting has an analytic core that sees the American Economic
 Association as an organization supplying goods and services to its
 members, one of which is the <em>Review</em>. Early in its history the
 <em>Review</em> was a multipurpose publication with highly disparate
 content. Over time the economics profession expanded and more economics
 research was produced, primarily in the form of journal articles. Editors
 accommodated this shift by allocating more resources to the refereeing and
 editing process and more space to research papers. (JEL A14, B19, B29)
