Author-Name: Paula Bustos  
Title: Trade Liberalization, Exports, and Technology Upgrading: Evidence on the Impact of MERCOSUR on Argentinian Firms 
Abstract:
 This paper studies the impact of a regional free trade agreement,
 MERCOSUR, on technology upgrading by Argentinean firms. To guide empirical
 work, I introduce technology choice in a model of trade with heterogeneous
 firms. The joint treatment of the technology and exporting choices shows
 that the increase in revenues produced by trade integration can induce
 exporters to upgrade technology. An empirical test of the model reveals
 that firms in industries facing higher reductions in Brazil's tariffs
 increase investment in technology faster. The effect of tariffs is highest
 in the upper-middle range of the firm-size distribution, as predicted by
 the model. (JEL F13, F15, O19, O24, O33)
